accessibility.text: Sudden gains and losses are usually observed in 17% to 50% of patients receiving psychotherapy, but they also occur in pharmalogical and placebo treatments
Note the parallel with the learning literature in developmental (e.g. Piaget) and cognitive psychology (e.g. aha-effects)
